  <metadata>
    <name><![CDATA[Lone Peak via Peak View and Jacob's Ladder Trail]]></name>
    <desc><![CDATA[]]></desc>
    <link href="http://www.alltrails.com">
      <text>AllTrails, LLC</text>
    </link>
    <bounds minlat="40.48646" minlon="-111.82018" maxlat="40.52858" maxlon="-111.75594"/>
  </metadata>
  <wpt lat="40.51415" lon="-111.78685">
    <name><![CDATA[Ennis Peak]]></name>
    <desc><![CDATA[]]></desc>
  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="40.5151" lon="-111.78055">
    <name><![CDATA[Stream]]></name>
    <desc><![CDATA[]]></desc>
  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="40.5151368" lon="-111.7789149">
    <name><![CDATA[Outlaw Cabin]]></name>
    <desc><![CDATA[There is a side trail to the left that heads to the Outlaw Cabin. To get to the summit, you'll head right instead: into the glacial cirque.]]></desc>
  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="40.526" lon="-111.76216">
    <name><![CDATA[Scrambling]]></name>
    <desc><![CDATA[From here, you will find your way via sections of scrambling that take you to the summit. Eventually, you will be scrambling over rocks to the top as the visible trail disappears. These final scrambles traverse sections that are very exposed to steep drop-offs. ]]></desc>
  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="40.52692" lon="-111.75587">
    <name><![CDATA[Summit of Lone Peak]]></name>
    <desc><![CDATA[You are at the top of this beautiful mountain standing above a huge glacial cirque that faces the valley and the town of Sandy.]]></desc>
  </wpt>
